    1440170423 => array(
        "There is no such thing as &ldquo;limited government,&rdquo; any more than there is such a thing as &ldquo;good government.&rdquo; ... I doubt that anybody in his right mind would favor unlimited government. But when you favor government, that&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;re doing. Because government, by its nature, is unlimited. You favor tyranny when you favor government; though you don&rsquo;t know it. This is why I am constantly staggered by those who say they are libertarian and are trying to set up their own particular way of providing a &ldquo;good government.&rdquo; It is a contradiction in terms. To say &ldquo;unlimited government&rdquo; is a redundancy and to say &ldquo;limited government&rdquo; is a contradiction. All you have to say is &ldquo;government.&rdquo; And that takes care of the whole thing.<br/>- Robert LeFevre, GOOD GOVERNMENT: HOPE OR ILLUSION? (From a Lecture at Santa Ana College, May 27, 1977); published by Rampart Institute Press, January 1978, page 19."
